crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a malicious stager/loader designed to resolve APIs dynamically and execute shellcode. It exhibits several high-confidence indicators of malware: 1) The entry point resides in a non-standard section ('.oymu') with Read-Write-Execute (RWX) permissions. 2) It implements a manual PEB (Process Environment Block) traversal routine using ROR13 hashing to locate and call Windows APIs by hash rather than name, a common technique to evade static analysis. 3) Decompilation of sub_1400050d6 shows references to 'ws2_32' (encoded as 0x32335f327377) and socket initialization, suggesting it connects to a remote server to download and execute further stages. 4) The code eventually performs a jump to a dynamically allocated/modified memory region, characteristic of shellcode execution.
